rows.content_default: I see those fools at the Abbey sent some fresh meat for us.
The Brotherhood will not tolerate your actions.
Ah, a chance to use this freshly sharpened blade.
Feel the power of the Brotherhood!
More bones to gnaw on...
Grrrr... fresh meat!
You no take candle!
Yiieeeee! Me run!
What aggravation is this? You will die!
Scream while you burn!
I'll incinerate you!
I revel in your pain!
You seek a prize, eh? How about death?
Your life will be mine!
I hate to say I told you so...
You won't... get far.
Insolent fool! You thought to steal Zelemar's blood? You shall pay with your own!
For Victory! For Agamaggan!
I'm gonna cook ya, and then i'm going to eat ya!
I hope you die! Painfully!
Mission accomplished.
VanCleef pay big for you heads!
Cipher of Damnation belongs to us now!
The master will know of this incursion. You will be hunted for all eternity!
You do not belong here!  Ancients, rise against these intruders!
You no challenge me, scrubs! I'm da king now, and I stay king FOREVER!!!
%s blood sprays into the air!
%s is splashed by the blood and becomes irradiated!
Electric justice!
Warning! Warning! Intruder alert! Intruder alert!
Step forward! I will see that you are properly welcomed.
Oh stop your whimpering.
I have not yet... begun to...
You are no longer dealing with some underling.
Band'or shorel'aran!
Guards! Come and kill these intruders!
Is this the end?
What will become of...
Time to join us, $c.
No!
I am finished!
The master... will be angry...
%s becomes enraged!
%s attempts to run away in fear!
You are spotted by the eye of Grillok!
Wait... No! No!
Not... Fair...
The fates have turned against me!
Where am I? What...
What is happening?
You... will... pay...
You will be punished!
Five seconds! I'm not kidding!
So I said, "Yeah, but that'll cost you extra."
He asked if the imp could join in... can you believe it? Actually, it wasn't half bad...
We could have had so much fun!
They fall asleep after. Me, I fall asleep during....
I'll miss the show!
Yes... I think I remember now...
It's all... coming back to me.
Is it really over?
Free... at last.
Time to move on...
Death is far too merciful for your kind.
The same fate awaits all who would steal from the master.
Others will take my place!
This... changes nothing. Eternal damnation awaits you!
Turn your back while you can!
You will succeed only in damning yourselves!
So dark...
Aaaaahhh! So close to escaping.
%s skitters out from the shadows...
Hey! Where do you think you are going, sneaking around like that?
Your strategy was flawed.
Yes, the only logical outcome.
An unforeseen... contingency.
Measure twice, cut once.
If my division is correct you should be quite dead.
I predict a painful death.
You should split while you can.
Damn, I'm good!
Bully!
Go ahead, gimme your best shot. I can take it!
Think you can hurt me, huh? Think I'm afraid of you?!
Can't say I didn't warn you!
The work must continue.
Don't make me kill you!
You brought this on yourselves.
It had to be done.
You should not have come.
I... Deserve this.
You will never wake the dreamer!
%s lets out a high pitched screech, calling for help!
For the Dragonmaw!
Long live the Dragonmaw! Die you worthless $r!
Brains...
This land belongs to the Dark Iron Dwarves. Prepare to see the afterlife, $c!
Your bones will break under my boot, $r!
%s goes into a frenzy!
Protect the innocent!
Serve the Public Trust!
Uphold the Law!
Take heart! Your friends will not long mourn your passing!
%s bursts, showering the area with arcane residue!
Your world is ours now.
More, more, more!  I must feed soon.
I cannot stand the pain.  I must find a new source.
Haven't you done enough harm?  Must you also disturb my slumber?
What good does this violence serve?  What is done is done.  I have failed my people.
Abandon all hope! The Legion has returned to finish what was begun so many years ago. This time, there will be no escape!
Reesh, hokta!
Just a taste... of what awaits you.
Don't fight it.
Your time is almost... up.
No one is going to save you.
I am the serpent king! I can do anything.
Insolence!

It will be much colder in your grave.
Crumble and rot!
Ashes to ashes, dust to dust.
All life must perish!
Victory to the Legion!
You have won this battle, but not... the... war.
Troublesome whelps. I'll teach you to interfere!
Our new allies  will avenge us!
You outsiders will pay for encroaching on our land!
Bah! My power rules here!
I will be reborn, mortals! Incendius shall raise me from these ashes!

The coils of death... Will crush you.
Invaders! Sound the Alarm!
Get it while it's hot!
Any intruders must be eliminated!
Protect the Botanica at all costs!
Protect the Mechanar at all costs!
You hear a faint unlocking sound...
The end is come!
Woot! Thanks!

I miss my dog so much...

Illidan reigns!

Lok Narash!
For Kargath! For Victory!
Lok'tar Illidari!
This world is OURS!
A living $r... soon to be a dead like me.
Mmm... I love my delicious Southshore stout.
Slay them, my brethren! For the Scourge!
We will enslave the quilboar!
We will spread across this barren land!
Soon, the Scourge will rule the world!
KILL!!!
Who dares disturb me?  Die $N!
None may challenge the Brotherhood!
And stay down!
Lapdogs, all of you!
Fools! Our cause is righteous!
The Brotherhood shall prevail!
You will suffer eternally!
Little creature made of flesh, your wish is granted! Death comes for you!

Looking for these???? You'll never have em!
Hold them back while I release the warhounds!
My pets are hungry and they will dine on your flesh!
We are the true Horde!
Mine! Mine! Mine! Gizlock is the ruler of this domain! You shall never reveal my presence!
What? Oh no. I don't care what you have to say. I just enjoy inflicting pain.

Confess and we shall set you free.

%s calls for his worgs!
A foul trogg if ever I saw one.  Die!

No gnome will be left behind.
The troggs...they never stop coming.  Die trogg!  Die!

Gizmos... check. Doothingies... check. Wizzers... check.
One day I'll be a real boy.
Brzt... click... whir...

We can make it better, stronger, faster. We have the technology. We have the magic.
You should not be here! Slay them!
Suffer you despicable insect!
You will be easy prey, $c.
My talons will shred your puny body, $r.
A fine trophy your head will make, $r.
NO!!!  It puts the tannin in the basket, or it gets the mallet again!
Fresh bread for sale!
Freshly baked bread for sale!
Shine yer armor for a copper?
Help a poor bloke out?
Some coin?

I'll deliver you, weak $c, to the afterlife!
Die in the name of Edwin van Cleef!
Crush!
Kill!
Destroy!

Your hopes are lost!
Scream for me!
Pity, no time for a slow death!

Pestilence upon you!

Sweet dreams...
Let fire rain from above!
Earth and sky shall burn!
I gonna make you into mojo!

You be dead soon!

%s bares her fangs and hisses menacingly at those around her.
%s focuses on $N.

The time of the Raven is night, but yours will end here!
You dare to disturb the loyal followers of the Raven?
You will die for your hubris, druid!
You dare to disturb the loyal followers of the Raven?
You will die for your hubris, druid!

C'mere, $r. Ya don't want to be riskin' yerself in a dungeon, do ya? Filthy work, and for what? Some worthless trinket? Nah, what ya need be one of my amulets. Guarenteed to work!

Dangerous out there, innit? Know what ya need? Protection. I can help ya defy death itself! Ya wear this madstone 'round yer neck, see, and then ya be able to come back if ya find yerself in the spirit world! Just a quick jaunt to yer corpse and up ya com

Amazing Amulets! Incredible curios! The newfangled jewelcrafters be havin' nothin' on the tried and true mystical methods of ol' Griftah! Improve yerself through these magical talismans for a bargain price!
I could have sworn I had more apples. Grok!
If no one help. Grok smash!
Look over here, $c! I got somethin' for ya. Just what ya need. It's soap, right... and it's on a rope! No offense, man, but yer a little ripe, you know what I'm sayin'?
Hey! Hey, $r! I be havin' just the thing for ya. Ya ever see a Tikbalang? Frightenin' creatures. Prone to stealin' ya away. What ya need is my tikbaland wards. Guaranteed to ward away all tikbalangs!

Mog'dorg the Wizened tell Grok go to city, get help for Bloodmaul. Grok go.
Bladespire clan not fight fair. Have Gronn to help dem. You go to Blade's Edge Mountains. Talk to Mog'dorg the Wizened. Kill Gromm.

Ya look tired, $c. I be havin' somethin' for ya. These amulets, they can help ya leap obstacles and swim through the rivers like ya be born to it. They energize the food ya be eatin'. Makin' yer wounds close before yer eyes!
What is that poor orc yelling about? Someone should see what is going on.
I feel that war is fast approaching. The fruit vendor has enlisted to help an ogre. I shall have to enlist help as well.
Ya look lovesick. Special someone be gettin' ya down, eh? No worries, no worries. Ya get this medallion from me, ya wear it when ya see 'em and they be all over ya, sweetheart!
Me hungry. Fruit look tasty.
FRUIT VENDOR!!! Your cart is still in our way! We will give you one more hour to move it from our area. Do not test our patience anymore!

Nothing like a tankard full to wash down one of my magnificent muffins.

I've got muffins right over here. Come on over!

All who venture here belong to me, including you!
Of course, my friend. How can I be of service to you?
A noble request. It would be an honor, Erothem.
My friends, please join me in humble supplication the the Light.
Light that we embrace, we beseech thee...
Into our struggle against the darkness we have sent our children.
Please bless and protect them, and grant them success over those who seek to do us harm...
Continue to bless this, our ancient home, we beg.
Bless us with tolerance for our elven visitors.
By the Naaru, may it be so.
%s nods.

But that's not the worst of it. Before I could pull us back, a group of 'em spotted us and attacked.
I dunno, grunt. I just - don't - know...
Fel orcs...
Big red bastards! Bigger than any orc I'd ever seen. Muscles out to here, tusks out to here...
Sure enough, scount came runnin' back, talkin' bout some orcs down the path. They hadn't seen us yet so we figured we'd go get aquainted.
So there we were - me and the battalion, doing a routine recon down the bone road. We'd sent the scout up ahead to look around in case anything dangerous come up.
Do I detect a hint of cinnamon? Or is that nutmeg? Whatever it is, one thing is for sure - nobody cooks donkey like you, Cookie.
If my stomach wasn't threatening to dislodge itself from my body and leave me for the refuse that we give to the prisoners, I might be insulted by this... this food.
And if I hear that you palookas complained to Nazgrel again, it'll be one of ya's that I serve up next time...
Yer slop is ready. Come n' get it...

You mean...

Yea, we got problems. I think that's crystal clear. The question is, what are we gonna do about it?

Do you not have eyes? Did you not see the demons on our very doorstep? I do not have the soldiers to spare!
Pray to your gods, shaman. Perhaps they will come to your aid. The Horde however, cannot...
Wow! Look at his muscles!
Will he win? Can he win?
He's so well disciplined!
I wanna be just like the pitfighter!
This one is slightly better than the last. However, it still suffers from the same flimsy bone structure as the others. When you summon one of these, you are on the right path.
How does he do it?
That's the best reward we're going to be able to offer. Hopefully someone accepts the mission.
Damm those ogres. Damn them to the Nether. Won't someone save us from these savages! This is the fifth kidnapping is as many days.
Any time any of you peons want to take a break, the graveyard is right over there.

Do you think that demons will play fair? These beasts are more savage than the orcs, more cunning than the undead. Do not attempt to engage Legion by normal standards of war.

This war - and don't mistake this for anything but war - is not going to win itself. If we do not fight, scratch, claw, and kick for every speck of land on this shattered world, all will be lost.

The creatures of this place are strong, wayfarer. You'll need ample ammunition if you hope to survive. You're in luck - I am well-stocked with fine arrows, bullets, and throwing weapons. The price is reasonable, considering the circumstances.
Ahh, another powerful traveler. The nether can be dangerous; you'll want the most potent spells at your disposal. I carry the finest reagents, common and exotic. Come and buy - you won't be sorry!

ATTENTION!
Alright, quiet down. We have a lot of work to do and very little time to do it in, people.
I've stood with some of you draenei before at Skettis, and others in Shadowmoon Valley. But now we're on Azeroth, and the situation looks grim.
First though, you sin'dorei listen up. I run a tight ship... this isn't going to be like what you're used to with the Scryers. Pull your weight, or get back on the boat!
Now that that's out of the way, welcome to the Isle of Quel'Danas. The Sunwell's on the plateau to the south, and Prince Kael'thas is holed up in the Magisters' Terrace to the east.
We're here as support for the so-called 'adventurers' that the brass called in. We'll help them hold the key points on the island, and keep the heat off so that they can do their jobs.
If none of you ladies have any questions, you can get further instruction and assignments from your squad leaders. That's it. Good luck!
Hearty Kill!
Welcome to the Sunwell. Despite the mild temperatures and scenic vistas, you're not on vacation, ladies and gentlemen!
The current situation looks like this: we're holding what we can while those with more experience and better equipment are moving against Prince Kael'thas.
I know, we thought he was dead too, but that's not the case. He's trying to use the Sunwell to bring the master of the Burning Legion, Kil'jaeden, into this world.
Let me assure you people that if he's successful, this world will suffer far worse than Outland ever did! So let's make sure that doesn't come to pass.
Warriors will be deployed to hold key positions, while you marksmen will be assigned to keep the enemy fliers at bay.
I'm awaiting orders on your specific assignments. In the meantime, stay here and be ready to move at a moment's notice!
Hello to you new recruits. I'm Drill Sergeant Bahduum. For the next few days, you're going to receive orientation.
The Isle of Quel'Danas has been overrun by the forces of Prince Kael'thas Sunstrider. Intel had him pegged as deceased. Intel was wrong.
Up on the plateau, he and his demon friends are trying to reignite the Sunwell and open a rift to bring their head-honcho, Kil'Jaeden back into the world.
Our job is to clear out as much of the fodder as we can, while supporting the specialists that the powers-that-be are having brought in.
Needless to say, a lot of us won't be going home. But if you remember your training and keep your wits about you, you'll greatly increase your chances.
That's all I have to say for now. Stay focused, boys and girls.
Shattered Sun scum! Fire at will!
Keep your eye on the demons. We're not concerned with killing Scourge today.
Dragonhawk incoming from the west! Shoot that druid down!
I cannot permit you to enter the temple! I must destroy you for your own good!

Never cross a Dark Iron, $c.

Beast! Obey me! Kill them at once!

Krypta!

Hal...
Yea, Nat?

Which one?
That one dream... The crazy one. Remember?
Tarren Mill is destroyed by some crazy force of undead and forever more becomes an enemy to Southshore.
Could ya imagine such a thing, Hal? Could ya?
Impossible!
That one where thousands of people are all watching us up from the sky...
We're like their puppets - we dance and cry and fight and say silly things for their amusement.
Sometimes, even when I'm awake, I think they're watching us. Maybe they're watching us right now...
Nat, I've heard a whopper or two in my day but that one takes the cake.
So I'm on some mountain with some big ol' tree. Bunch of elves runnin' around all over...
Out of nowhere, some 300 foot tall demon or somethin' walks up and starts climbin' the tree...
And if that weren't crazy enough, that big demon gets killed by a bunch of floating light things... Oh, I was also a female elf in that one... Yep...
In this dream, I was fishin' master of the world. I moved to some place called Kalimdor...
And people from all over the world come to me to pay homage... and learn to fish.
I'm like some kind of fishing god...
This one's real grim... So the king's kid Arthas...Well he goes out to battle evil, along with Uther *Nat pats his brow dry*
But tragically, Arthas is consumed by the evil and becomes evil himself...
